  <description><![CDATA[<p>The comfortable Hotel New Solarium set in <a data-udi="umb://document/9e7d0f01e7964af0b7ee7c501cb0e893" href="/{localLink:umb://document/9e7d0f01e7964af0b7ee7c501cb0e893}" title="Courchevel">Courchevel</a> 1850 has everything you need for a relaxing week in <a data-udi="umb://document/bd152c97eb204c59a0ae4a5b65e2c1e5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/bd152c97eb204c59a0ae4a5b65e2c1e5}" title="France">France</a>. After a day on the mountain you can make the most of the well-being area which includes a heated swimming pool, sauna and hammam - plus if you want to stay active there is also a fitness area. There's a cosy lounge bar with a fireplace, and fabulous mountain views.</p>
<h2>Access to the Three Valleys Area</h2>
<p>If you are looking for a cosy and comfortable hotel with access to the extensive <a data-udi="umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578" href="/{localLink:umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578}" title="Three Valleys Ski Area">Three Valleys Ski Area</a>, the New Solarium is an excellent choice. The Jardin Alpin lift is just a short walk away, and you can basically ski in/out via the green piste nearby. </p>
<h2>Soothing spa and swimming pool</h2>
<p>The Hotel New Solarium ticks all the boxes for a winter getaway, as well as having a central location in Courchevel 1850, you can make the most of the wellness facilities included with your stay. Have a dip in the heated indoor pool or unwind in the sauna and hammam when you return from exploring the Three Valleys. For a little extra indulgence, massages and beauty treatments are available for a local cost. If skiing or snowboarding hasn't worn you out there's also a fitness area with a range of equipment. </p>
<h2>Food and drink </h2>
<p>The cosy lounge bar is the ideal spot to enjoy a glass of wine after a day on the slopes or an aperitif before dinner. With a central fireplace and scenic views of the resort it's a great place to catch up with family and friends. When it comes to dinner, you can enjoy tasty French dishes and Savoyard specialities in the hotels restaurant which you can book and pay for locally, or explore the rest of Courchevel 1850.</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
